The paper discusses the use of hyper-heuristics, which are a type of artificial intelligence methodology, for solving combinatorial optimization problems. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks, which is a subfield of both machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also involves experimentation and analysis of results, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE).
